U.S. Stock-Index Futures Rebound as China Cuts its Lenders’ Reserve Ratio

-- B y   A d a m   H a i g h
-- 
2011-11-30T11:11:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-11-30/u-s-stock-index-futures-strengthen-after-china-cuts-banks-reserve-ratio.html
U.S. stock-index futures rose,
reversing earlier losses, after  China ’s central bank said it
will cut the reserve requirement ratio for banks by 0.5
percentage points from Dec. 5.  Futures contracts on the Standard & Poor’s 500 Index
expiring in December climbed 0.4 percent to 1,201.50 as of 6:08
a.m. in  New York , having earlier fallen as much as 1.1 percent.  The People’s Bank of China made a statement on its website
today.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Adam Haigh at 
 ahaigh1@bloomberg.net  